<title>USA: PCX to trade Information Management options.</title>
<headline>PCX to trade Information Management options.</headline>
<dateline>SAN FRANCISCO 1997-08-11</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Pacific Exchange (PCX) said Monday it will list options on Information Management Resources Inc on August 15.</p>
<p>The options will open with strike prices of 30, 35 and 40, with position limits of 7,500 contracts. Initial expirations will be in September, October, November and February.</p>
<p>The options have been allocated to lead market makers Rob Kovell and Tom Valenzuela.</p>
<p>The options will also trade on the American Stock Exchange and the Chicago Board Options Exchange.</p>
<p>((--Chicago derivatives desk, 312 408 8750))</p>
